imdb.plot outline: Las Vegas is a family of four women, the mother and three daughters, forced to take over a very peculiar business to pay the deceased father's debts: a women's night club. The supposedly perfect father and husband, who died under very suspicious circumstances, leaves them with no money, lots of debts and lots of secrets that will emerge little by little: a double life, a second family, a group of mobster friends... and a night club. Las Vegas will have to leave their shame and moral aside to take forward this particular venture or to risk and lose everything. Not only will they were with a group of inexperienced "strippers" but they will risk the very little stability left in their lives by dealing with the prejudices of those around them and resist the temptation and not get carried away by their own passion. By working in the industry of sensuality, these women begin a journey of liberation and independence that will change their lives forever.
imdb.title: Las Vega's
plot: The women of the Vegas family are full of debts, for this reason they decide to hire a group of male strippers and open a night club dedicated to the female audience.::Anonymous
